choices.text: You are given a function $f : \{0,1,2, \cdots, p - 1 \} \rightarrow \{0,1,2, \cdots, p - 1 \}$. Find the number of distinct functions $f$ that satisfy the equation $f(k x \operatorname{mod} p) \equiv k \cdot f(x) \operatorname{mod} p$ for all integers x in the range 0 to p - 1, inclusive.
